---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Consentus is the trusted layer for surgical informed consent in the UK — built with named clinicians, owned by no one, accountable to patients."
>
  <article class="about container">
    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>The trusted layer for surgical informed consent.</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p class="lead">
        Surgeons have ten to fifteen minutes to explain procedures that take
        years to learn. Patients sign forms they don't fully understand. The
        result is poorer decisions, more complaints, and more litigation.
        Consentus exists to do better.
      </p>

      <h2>What we are</h2>
      <p>
        Consentus is a free, public library of surgical procedure videos and
        FAQs, made by named UK consultants. Each procedure page is authored
        and reviewed by a practising specialist with their GMC registration on
        the page. The editorial bar is rigour, not engagement.
      </p>

      <h2>What we are not</h2>
      <p>
        We are not a content channel, a clinic, or a medical advice service.
        We do not replace your consultant. We do not run ads, and we do not
        track patients across the web. The site exists so that the
        conversation in the consulting room can start ten minutes further
        along than it would have otherwise.
      </p>

      <h2>How we sustain ourselves</h2>
      <p>
        The patient-facing library is, and will remain, free. Consentus Ltd is
        a private company building a commercial platform sold to hospitals and
        private clinics — embedding the same clinical content into their
        consent pathway, with comprehension-verified audit trails for the
        record. The free side earns the trust. The paid side funds the work.
      </p>

      <h2>Our standard</h2>
      <p>
        Consentus is pursuing B Corp certification. Independent of that, we
        commit to: every procedure page authored by a named UK consultant; a
        last-reviewed date on every page, with annual review at minimum; no
        third-party tracking on patient-facing pages; and clear disclosure of
        any clinical or commercial relationship that could affect editorial
        content.
      </p>

      <h2>Founder</h2>
      <p>
        Consentus was founded in 2026 by [Founder name], based in London. The
        company is incorporated as Consentus Ltd in England and Wales.
      </p>

      <h2>Advisory board</h2>
      <p>
        Names announced as the founding advisory board is finalised. If you
        are a UK consultant interested in contributing —
        <a href="/for-clinicians">we'd like to talk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        General enquiries:
        <a href="mailto:info@consentus.org">info@consentus.org</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .page-header .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    max-width: 32rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem !important;
    line-height: 1.55 !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 18;
  }
</style>
